{'hadithnumber': 1, 'text': 'The report is not like witnessing'}
{'hadithnumber': 2, 'text': 'War is deception'}
{'hadithnumber': 3, 'text': 'A Muslim is a mirror of the Muslim'}
{'hadithnumber': 4, 'text': 'Someone whose advice is sought is in a position of trust'}
{'hadithnumber': 5, 'text': 'The person guiding (someone) to do a good deed, is like the one performing the good deed'}
{'hadithnumber': 6, 'text': 'Seek help for any needs discreetly'}
{'hadithnumber': 7, 'text': 'Protect yourself from the fire even with a part of a date'}
{'hadithnumber': 8, 'text': 'The world is the believer’s prison and the disbeliever’s paradise'}
{'hadithnumber': 9, 'text': 'Modesty is entirely good'}
{'hadithnumber': 10, 'text': 'The word of the believer is like seizing of the hand'}
{'hadithnumber': 11, 'text': 'It is unlawful for a believer to sever relations with his brother for more than three days'}
{'hadithnumber': 12, 'text': 'He is not one of us who cheats us'}
{'hadithnumber': 13, 'text': 'A little that suffices is better than an abundance that distracts'}
{'hadithnumber': 14, 'text': 'Someone who takes back his gift is like someone who eats his vomit'}
{'hadithnumber': 15, 'text': 'Affliction comes from (loose) talk'}
{'hadithnumber': 16, 'text': 'People are like the teeth of a comb'}
{'hadithnumber': 17, 'text': 'Richness lies in the richness of the soul'}
{'hadithnumber': 18, 'text': 'The felicitous person takes lessons from (the actions of) others'}
{'hadithnumber': 19, 'text': 'Indeed, in poetry there is wisdom and in eloquence there is magic'}
{'hadithnumber': 20, 'text': 'The king’s pardon preserves the kingdom'}
{'hadithnumber': 21, 'text': 'A man will be with whom he loves'}
{'hadithnumber': 22, 'text': 'A man who knows his worth will not be ruined'}
{'hadithnumber': 23, 'text': 'The child belongs to the bed and stoning is for the adulterer'}
{'hadithnumber': 24, 'text': 'The upper hand is superior to the lower hand'}
{'hadithnumber': 25, 'text': 'He does not thank Allah who does not thank people'}
{'hadithnumber': 26, 'text': 'Your love of something can blind and deafen (you)'}
{'hadithnumber': 27, 'text': 'Hearts are predisposed to love someone who does them good and detest someone who does them harm'}
{'hadithnumber': 28, 'text': 'One who repents from sin is like someone without sin'}
{'hadithnumber': 29, 'text': 'The person who actually witnesses an (event) sees that which one who is absent does not'}
{'hadithnumber': 30, 'text': 'If the nobleman of a people comes to you, honour him'}
{'hadithnumber': 31, 'text': 'False oaths lay waste to home (lands)'}
{'hadithnumber': 32, 'text': 'Whoever is killed attempting to save his property is a martyr'}
{'hadithnumber': 33, 'text': 'Actions are through intentions'}
{'hadithnumber': 34, 'text': 'The leader of a people is their servant'}
{'hadithnumber': 35, 'text': 'The best of affairs is that which is balanced'}
{'hadithnumber': 36, 'text': 'O Allah, bless my nation in its early rising on Thursdays'}
{'hadithnumber': 37, 'text': 'Poverty can almost turn into disbelief'}
{'hadithnumber': 38, 'text': 'Travelling is a portion of punishment'}
{'hadithnumber': 39, 'text': 'The best of provision is God-Consciousness (taqwa)'}
{'hadithnumber': 40, 'text': 'Meetings are under trust'}
